Caffe Parser¶

turret.caffe.caffe¶

class turret.caffe.caffe.CaffeParser¶

Bases: object

Class used for parsing Caffe models. Allows users to export models trained using Caffe to TRT.

parse()¶

Parse a prototxt file and a binaryproto Caffe model to extract network configuration and weights associated with the network, respectively.

Parameters

  • network (turret.NetworkDefinition) – The network in which the CaffeParser will fill the layers.

  • deploy (str) – The plain text, prototxt file used to define the network configuration.

  • model (str) – The binaryproto Caffe model that contains the weights associated with the network.

Returns

tensorset(turret.NamedTensorSet) – The object that contains the extracted data.

set_plugin_factory()¶

Set the plugin factory to parser.

Parameters

factory (turret.PluginFactory) – The plugin factory.

class turret.caffe.caffe.NamedTensorSet¶

Bases: object

The object that contains the data extracted from caffe model. This object can be used as dictionary, and The data got from this object is turret.Tensor.

turret.caffe.caffe.import_caffemodel()¶

Import caffe model to Turret.

Parameters

  • network (turret.NetworkDefinition) – The network in which the CaffeParser will fill the layers.

  • deploy (str) – The plain text, prototxt file used to define the network configuration.

  • model (str) – The binaryproto Caffe model that contains the weights associated with the network.

  • plugin_factory (turret.PluginFactory, optional) – The plugin factory. Default to None.

Returns

tensorset(turret.NamedTensorSet) – The object that contains the extracted data.

The PluginFactory for caffe model.

create(layer_name, weights)¶

Create the plugin.

Parameters

  • layer_name (str) – The name of layer.

  • weights (turret.Weights) – The weight parameter for the layer.

Returns

plugin(turret.PluginProxy) – The plugin object for the layer.

is_plugin(layer_name)¶

Check whether the layer is in the plugin factory.

Parameters

layer_name (str) – The name of layer.

Returns

result(bool) – true if the layer name is in the plugin factory.

register_plugin(layer_name, factory)¶

Register the plugin.

Parameters

  • layer_name (str) – The name of layer.

  • factory – The object of plugin.
